# Cursor Rules for ReadSync

## Project
ReadSync — Go 1.22+ Windows reading-progress sync service.
Module: github.com/readsync/readsync
Full guide: AGENTS.md

## Language & style
- Go 1.22+ only
- gofmt/goimports always
- Error strings: lowercase, no trailing period
- No panic() in production code
- Package names: singular (model, outbox, resolver)
- Black-box tests: package foo_test

## Architecture rules
- Domain types: internal/model/model.go only
- Pipeline writes: only via core.Pipeline.Submit()
- Migrations: APPEND-ONLY to internal/db/migrations.go
- Admin UI: always bind to 127.0.0.1, never 0.0.0.0
- CSRF: every write endpoint needs requireCSRF(s.csrfToken, handler)
- Secrets: internal/secrets/ only, never hardcode
- Logging: internal/logging/ only, never log.Printf
- No Goodreads API HTTP calls

## CGO split
Pure-Go (no CGO allowed):
  internal/adapters/calibre/opf/
  internal/adapters/koreader/codec/
  internal/adapters/moon/
  internal/resolver/
  internal/conflicts/
  internal/logging/
  internal/setup/
  internal/repair/
  internal/secrets/
  internal/api/
  tests/security/

CGO required (go-sqlite3):
  internal/db/
  internal/core/
  internal/adapters/calibre/ (parent)
  internal/adapters/koreader/ (parent)
  tests/integration/

## Key files
internal/model/model.go         - all domain types
internal/adapters/adapter.go    - Adapter/EventEmitter/WriteTarget interfaces
internal/resolver/resolver.go   - Score(), Band(), WritebackEnabled()
internal/conflicts/engine.go    - DetectSuspiciousJump(), CanAutoResolve()
internal/outbox/worker.go       - NextRetry(), Enqueue(), Worker
internal/api/server.go          - Server, CSRFHeader constant
internal/logging/redact.go      - IsSecretKey(), add new secret keys here
internal/db/migrations.go       - APPEND ONLY, never modify existing

## Test commands
make test-unit              # no CGO
make test-phase7-unit       # all no-CGO packages
make test-security          # CSRF + redaction
make test-integration       # CGO required
make test                   # all

